            <title>[SOLR-15871] Update Log4J2 version to  2.17.1</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-15871</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Upgrade log4j even if &lt;a href=&quot;https://solr.apache.org/security.html#apache-solr-affected-by-apache-log4j-cve-2021-44228&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Solr is not affected by the latest CVE&lt;/a&gt;. Main reason to upgrade is so that the next Solr release will no longer produce false positives in primitive security scanner tools for log4j.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;Originalreport%3A&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Original report:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;High security vulnerability in Log4J - CVE-2021-45105 bundled with Solr&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
